  "text": "SPECjvm98. Figure 7 presents comparison of the age-oriented collector with the original collector and with the generational collector over all the suite's benchmarks [CITATION_1] . When running the SPECjvm98 benchmarks on a multiprocessor, the collector thread can run on a designated processor and hardly influence the throughput [CITATION_2] . The results show that the age-oriented collector performs slightly better than both the original collector and the generational collector. Large variations in performance are especially noticeable with 213 javac. The reason for these fluctuations is that 213 javac creates many garbage cycles in the old generation. All three collectors (the age-oriented, the generational and the original) rely on a backup tracing collector to collect these cycles. Collection of these cycles is triggered at irregular times resulting in the observed fluctuations.",
